  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.florida', NULL, 'Which reptile is a common animal found in Florida''s wetlands and swamps?', '["Camel","Polar bear","Penguin","Alligator"]', 3, 'Alligators live in Florida''s warm wetlands and swamps.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A high, flat area of land that rises above the land around it is a ___.', '["river","bay","plateau","valley"]', 2, 'A plateau is raised land that is flat on top.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A part of the ocean or a lake that curves into the land is a ___.', '["bay","plain","hill","forest"]', 0, 'A bay is a body of water that is partly surrounded by curving land.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A body of fresh water with land all around it is a ___.', '["ocean","gulf","lake","sea"]', 2, 'A lake is a body of water surrounded by land.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A dry place that gets very little rain and may be sandy is a ___.', '["wetland","forest","desert","glacier"]', 2, 'A desert is a very dry place with little rainfall.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A small pool of water surrounded by land, smaller than a lake, is a ___.', '["sea","ocean","gulf","pond"]', 3, 'A pond is a small body of still water smaller than a lake.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.maptools', NULL, 'On most maps, which direction is to your RIGHT when north is up?', '["West","East","Down","South"]', 1, 'When north is at the top of a map, east is on the right side.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.maptools', NULL, 'The directions in between the cardinal directions, like northeast, are called ___ directions.', '["corner-only","upside-down","middle-line","intermediate"]', 3, 'Intermediate directions are the in-between ones such as northeast and southwest.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.maptools', NULL, 'If you are facing north and turn all the way around to face the opposite way, you are facing ___.', '["south","north","west","east"]', 0, 'South is the opposite of north.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.maptools', NULL, 'A tool with a magnetic needle that always points north to help you find your way is a ___.', '["calendar","ruler","compass","camera"]', 2, 'A compass has a needle that points north to help you find directions.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.maptools', NULL, 'Which direction would you travel to go from the top of a map toward the bottom (when north is up)?', '["West","South","North","East"]', 1, 'Going from the top toward the bottom of a north-up map means traveling south.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.usregions', NULL, 'Florida is part of which region of the United States?', '["Midwest","Southeast","Northwest","Pacific Northwest"]', 1, 'Florida is located in the Southeast region of the United States.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.usregions', NULL, 'One of the longest rivers in the United States, flowing through the middle of the country, is the ___ River.', '["Nile","Thames","Amazon","Mississippi"]', 3, 'The Mississippi River flows through the middle of the United States.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.usregions', NULL, 'The flat, grassy farming region in the middle of the country is known as the ___.', '["Rocky Coast","Great Lakes","Great Plains","Sandy Desert"]', 2, 'The Great Plains are wide, flat grasslands in the central United States.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.usregions', NULL, 'On which continent is the United States located?', '["Europe","Asia","Africa","North America"]', 3, 'The United States is part of the continent of North America.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.usregions', NULL, 'States in the central part of the country, like Iowa and Kansas, are part of the ___.', '["Southwest","Northeast","Midwest","West Coast"]', 2, 'Iowa, Kansas, and nearby central states make up the Midwest region.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.florida', NULL, 'The narrow strip of land in northwest Florida is nicknamed the ___.', '["Delta","Peninsula","Panhandle","Isthmus"]', 2, 'The long, thin northwest part of Florida is called the Panhandle because it looks like a pan''s handle.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.florida', NULL, 'What kind of weather does most of Florida have?', '["Warm and rainy","Cold and snowy","Cool and windy all year","Dry and freezing"]', 0, 'Florida has a warm climate with lots of rain, especially in summer.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.florida', NULL, 'The large wetland of grassy water in south Florida is sometimes called the ''River of Grass.'' Its name is the ___.', '["Mojave","Great Plains","Outback","Everglades"]', 3, 'The Everglades is a wide, grassy wetland in south Florida known as the River of Grass.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.florida', NULL, 'Florida is mostly flat, so it has very few ___.', '["beaches","lakes","mountains","cities"]', 2, 'Florida''s land is low and flat, so it has almost no mountains.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A large, slow-moving body of ice on land is a ___.', '["lake","glacier","desert","gulf"]', 1, 'A glacier is a huge mass of ice that slowly moves over land.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A steep, high rock face, often near the ocean, is a ___.', '["meadow","cliff","delta","valley"]', 1, 'A cliff is a tall, steep face of rock or land.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'A long, narrow lowland between mountains or hills is a ___.', '["peninsula","plateau","cliff","valley"]', 3, 'A valley is the low land found between hills or mountains.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'Land with many trees growing close together is a ___.', '["plateau","plain","desert","forest"]', 3, 'A forest is a large area of land covered with trees.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.landforms', NULL, 'The line where the land meets the sea is called the ___.', '["coast","valley","plateau","peak"]', 0, 'The coast is the edge of land along the ocean.', 10),
  ('geography', '3', 2, 'geo.3.maptools', NULL, 'The little box on a map that lists what the symbols mean is called the map ___.', '["border","corner","key","title"]', 2, 'The map key, or legend, explains what the map''s symbols stand for.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'The very first people to live in Florida long ago were ___.', '["factory workers","Native Americans","train engineers","astronauts"]', 1, 'Native American peoples lived in Florida long before others arrived.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans long ago got their food by ___.', '["using vending machines","hunting, fishing, and farming","ordering pizza","shopping at stores"]', 1, 'They hunted, fished, and grew crops for food.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'An explorer is a person who ___.', '["bakes bread","fixes cars","travels to learn about new places","teaches math"]', 2, 'Explorers travel to discover and learn about places new to them.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Long ago, Spanish explorers sailed to Florida across the ___ Ocean.', '["Atlantic","Arctic","Indian","Pacific"]', 0, 'Explorers from Spain crossed the Atlantic Ocean to reach Florida.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'St. Augustine, Florida, is known as the oldest ___ in the United States.', '["river","city","school","mountain"]', 1, 'St. Augustine is the oldest continuously settled city in the U.S.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'The name ''Florida'' comes from a word that means ___.', '["tall mountains","full of flowers","big city","very cold"]', 1, 'Spanish explorers named it ''La Florida,'' meaning full of flowers.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'A line that shows events in the order they happened is a ___.', '["timeline","map key","grid","compass"]', 0, 'A timeline lists events in the order they happened.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'On a timeline, events on the LEFT usually happened ___ events on the right.', '["at the same time as","after","before","instead of"]', 2, 'Timelines go in order, so earlier events are to the left.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Long ago, Spanish settlers built forts in Florida out of a stone called ___.', '["marble","ice","gold","coquina"]', 3, 'The fort in St. Augustine was built from coquina, a local shell stone.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Explorers used a tool called a ___ to find directions at sea.', '["calendar","thermometer","compass","telescope only"]', 2, 'A compass helped sailors know which way they were heading.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'If you list your birthdays in order from age 1 to now, you are making a ___.', '["shopping list","graph of weather","timeline","map"]', 2, 'Putting events in time order makes a timeline.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Christopher Columbus sailed across the ocean in the year ___.', '["1620","1492","1776","1865"]', 1, 'Columbus made his famous voyage across the Atlantic in 1492.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Long ago, explorers crossed the ocean from Europe by traveling in ___.', '["trains","airplanes","sailing ships","cars"]', 2, 'Explorers long ago crossed the ocean in wooden sailing ships.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Which body of water did European explorers cross to reach the Americas?', '["the Atlantic Ocean","a river","a small pond","a swimming pool"]', 0, 'Explorers from Europe crossed the wide Atlantic Ocean.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Why was sailing across the ocean dangerous for explorers long ago?', '["too many traffic lights","too much homework","storms and long trips with little food","the trip took only one hour"]', 2, 'Long ocean voyages had storms and often ran low on food and fresh water.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'The flag that the first explorers of Florida planted belonged to ___.', '["Mexico","Spain","Russia","Brazil"]', 1, 'Spain was the first European country to explore and claim Florida.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'The first people to live in North America long, long ago were the ___.', '["Spanish sailors","English colonists","Native Americans","French traders"]', 2, 'Native Americans lived in North America long before explorers arrived.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Many Native American groups long ago got food by hunting, fishing, and ___.', '["buying cans","baking in ovens","using grocery stores","growing crops"]', 3, 'Many Native peoples grew crops such as corn, beans, and squash.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans long ago hunted animals to get food and ___.', '["gasoline","materials for clothing","cell phones","electricity"]', 1, 'Hunting gave Native peoples both food and skins for clothing.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native peoples in Florida used shells and bones to make ___.', '["tools","plastic toys","computers","light bulbs"]', 0, 'Florida''s Native peoples shaped shells and bones into useful tools.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans hunted deer using a ___.', '["computer","bow and arrow","shopping cart","skateboard"]', 1, 'Native hunters often used a bow and arrow to hunt animals like deer.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Which large body of water is on the WEST side of Florida?', '["the Pacific Ocean","the Arctic Ocean","the Gulf of Mexico","a small lake"]', 2, 'The Gulf of Mexico lies along Florida''s western coast.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'The Seminole are a Native American group connected to the history of ___.', '["Maine","Alaska","Hawaii","Florida"]', 3, 'The Seminole are a Native American people of Florida.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Which group of people lived in Florida FIRST, before settlers came from Europe?', '["English farmers","French sailors","Spanish soldiers","Native Americans"]', 3, 'Native Americans lived in Florida before any Europeans arrived.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Florida is the southeastern part of which country?', '["the United States","Spain","Canada","Mexico"]', 0, 'Florida is a state in the southeastern United States.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'A time that has already happened is called the ___.', '["next week","tomorrow","past","future"]', 2, 'The past is the time that has already happened.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'A group of 10 years is called a ___.', '["second","minute","decade","week"]', 2, 'A decade is a period of 10 years.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'The words ''long ago'' on a timeline point to events in the ___.', '["next year","past","tomorrow","future"]', 1, 'Long ago means events that happened in the past.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Which of these is a way to show events in the order they happened?', '["a timeline","a backpack","a paintbrush","a lunchbox"]', 0, 'A timeline shows events in the order they happened.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'The day that comes right after today is called ___.', '["long ago","tomorrow","last week","yesterday"]', 1, 'Tomorrow is the day right after today.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Christopher Columbus sailed for which country?', '["Spain","Egypt","Canada","Japan"]', 0, 'The king and queen of Spain paid for Columbus''s voyage.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'What is the main reason explorers sailed to new lands long ago?', '["to watch television","to play video games","to find new routes and riches","to go to school"]', 2, 'Explorers sailed to find new trade routes, land, and riches.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'An explorer is a person who travels to ___.', '["stay home all day","build only houses","learn about new and unknown places","sell only food"]', 2, 'An explorer travels to discover and learn about unknown places.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Which of these people was a famous explorer?', '["Abraham Lincoln","Christopher Columbus","Benjamin Franklin","Betsy Ross"]', 1, 'Christopher Columbus was a famous explorer who sailed across the Atlantic.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'In what year did Ponce de Leon reach Florida?', '["1513","1865","1969","1776"]', 0, 'Ponce de Leon reached Florida in the year 1513.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Which group lived in Florida long ago, before the Spanish arrived?', '["the Romans","the Timucua","the Vikings","the Pilgrims"]', 1, 'The Timucua were a Native people who lived in Florida long before the Spanish.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Which of these did Native Americans long ago use to travel on rivers?', '["canoes","buses","cars","subway trains"]', 0, 'Native peoples carved canoes from logs to travel on rivers and lakes.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'The Apalachee people lived in which part of North America?', '["the deserts of Egypt","an island in Asia","far northern Canada","northern Florida"]', 3, 'The Apalachee were a Native people who lived in northern Florida.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Many different Native American groups each had their own language and ___.', '["video games","factories","airplanes","customs"]', 3, 'Each Native group had its own language and special customs.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Why did some Native American groups move with the seasons?', '["to visit amusement parks","to follow food sources like animals and plants","to go to a new school","to watch a parade"]', 1, 'Some groups moved to follow animals and ripe plants for food.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'St. Augustine, Florida, was founded by settlers from ___.', '["Italy","Spain","England","France"]', 1, 'Spanish settlers founded St. Augustine in 1565.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'For many years long ago, Florida was ruled by the country of ___.', '["Spain","Australia","Germany","Japan"]', 0, 'Spain ruled Florida for hundreds of years before it became a U.S. state.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Which fruit is an important crop grown in Florida?', '["apples on cactus","bananas on pine trees","oranges","pineapples grown in snow"]', 2, 'Florida is famous for growing oranges and other citrus fruit.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'What is one reason many people move to Florida today?', '["its lack of water","its tall snowy mountains","its long, freezing winters","its warm, sunny weather"]', 3, 'Many people move to Florida for its warm, sunny weather.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Before Florida was a state, it was a U.S. ___.', '["planet","territory","country","city"]', 1, 'Florida was a U.S. territory before it became a state in 1845.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'A time that has not happened yet is called the ___.', '["past","long ago","yesterday","future"]', 3, 'The future is the time that has not happened yet.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'A group of 100 years is called a ___.', '["day","century","decade","hour"]', 1, 'A century is a period of 100 years.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'If you were born, then started school, then turned nine, which happened FIRST?', '["you were born","you turned ten","you turned nine","you started school"]', 0, 'Being born happened before starting school or turning nine.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Putting events in the order they happened is called putting them in ___.', '["alphabetical order only","a pile","order by time","a circle"]', 2, 'Putting events in the order they happened means ordering them by time.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Which of these belongs to the FUTURE?', '["yesterday''s lunch","the day you were born","a trip you will take next year","a trip you took last summer"]', 2, 'Something that will happen next year is in the future.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'The explorer who reached Florida in 1513 and gave it its name was ___.', '["Abraham Lincoln","George Washington","Ponce de Leon","Daniel Boone"]', 2, 'Ponce de Leon, a Spanish explorer, reached Florida in 1513 and named it.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Columbus was looking for a new way to sail to ___ when he crossed the Atlantic.', '["the Moon","Texas","Florida","Asia"]', 3, 'Columbus hoped to find a shorter sea route to Asia.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'The Spanish explorer who marched far through Florida and the Southeast looking for gold was ___.', '["Paul Revere","Henry Ford","Hernando de Soto","Thomas Edison"]', 2, 'Hernando de Soto led a Spanish journey through Florida and the Southeast.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Spanish explorers came to Florida from the continent of ___.', '["Africa","Australia","Europe","Antarctica"]', 2, 'Spanish explorers sailed to Florida from Europe.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Explorers wrote down what they saw on their trips in a ___.', '["kite","blanket","sandwich","journal"]', 3, 'Explorers kept journals to record what they saw and did.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'The Calusa people of South Florida got much of their food by ___.', '["fishing in the sea","farming in the snow","ordering pizza","driving to a store"]', 0, 'The Calusa were skilled fishers who caught much of their food from the sea.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans long ago learned about their history by ___.', '["telling stories out loud","listening to the radio","reading websites","watching television"]', 0, 'Native peoples passed down their history through spoken stories.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'What kind of homes did many Native American groups build long ago?', '["homes made from wood, grass, and other natural materials","tall brick skyscrapers","metal trailers","plastic tents from a store"]', 0, 'Native peoples built homes from natural materials like wood and grass.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans long ago depended on the ___ around them for food and shelter.', '["shopping malls","movie theaters","gas stations","land and water"]', 3, 'Native peoples used the land and water around them to live.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans were living in Florida ___ the Spanish explorers arrived.', '["after","instead of","because","before"]', 3, 'Native peoples were already living in Florida before the Spanish came.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Florida became the 27th state of the United States in ___.', '["1969","1492","1776","1845"]', 3, 'Florida joined the United States as the 27th state in 1845.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'What does the name ''Florida'' mean?', '["land of flowers","land of deserts","land of mountains","land of ice"]', 0, 'Florida comes from a Spanish word meaning full of flowers.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Long ago, why did Spain want to keep Florida?', '["to build snow resorts","to mine for gold in the mountains","to protect its ships sailing nearby","to grow apples"]', 2, 'Florida helped Spain guard its ships traveling through nearby waters.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Spanish settlers in early Florida often built strong forts to ___.', '["play sports","grow flowers","protect their towns","store ice cream"]', 2, 'Forts helped Spanish settlers protect their towns from attack.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Which ocean borders the EAST coast of Florida?', '["the Pacific Ocean","the Atlantic Ocean","the Arctic Ocean","the Indian Ocean"]', 1, 'The Atlantic Ocean lies along Florida''s eastern coast.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Which event happened FIRST?', '["The United States was born in 1776","Columbus sailed across the ocean in 1492","Florida became a state in 1845","People landed on the Moon in 1969"]', 1, 'The year 1492 came before 1776, 1845, and 1969.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Which of these came BEFORE the United States was born in 1776?', '["People landed on the Moon in 1969","Florida became a state in 1845","Columbus sailed in 1492","Cars filled the roads in the 1900s"]', 2, 'The year 1492 came before 1776.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Which word tells about something happening RIGHT NOW?', '["past","yesterday","future","present"]', 3, 'The present is the time happening right now.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'Which event happened the LONGEST time ago?', '["Columbus sailed in 1492","people landed on the Moon in 1969","Florida became a state in 1845","airplanes were invented in the 1900s"]', 0, '1492 is the earliest of these dates, so it was longest ago.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.timeline', NULL, 'People landed on the Moon in 1969. Was this before or after Florida became a state in 1845?', '["never","at the same time","after","before"]', 2, '1969 came after 1845, so the Moon landing happened later.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'When Columbus crossed the ocean in 1492, he landed on islands in the ___.', '["mountains","desert","Arctic","Caribbean"]', 3, 'Columbus first landed on islands in the Caribbean Sea.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Explorers who sailed for Spain often claimed new land for their ___.', '["teacher","pet","neighbor","king and queen"]', 3, 'Spanish explorers claimed new lands for the king and queen of Spain.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'What did explorers use a map for?', '["to help find their way","to cook dinner","to tell jokes","to keep warm"]', 0, 'Explorers used maps to help find their way to new places.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.explorers', NULL, 'Which sentence about explorers is TRUE?', '["They sailed to places that were new to them","They traveled only by airplane","They never crossed any water","They all stayed in one town forever"]', 0, 'Explorers traveled to lands that were new and unknown to them.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native Americans long ago made their clothing mostly from ___.', '["rubber and foam","plastic and metal","glass and paper","animal skins and plants"]', 3, 'Native peoples made clothing from animal skins and plant materials.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'A crop that many Native American groups grew for food was ___.', '["cereal in a box","candy","ice cream","corn"]', 3, 'Corn was an important food crop grown by many Native peoples.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Which sentence about Native Americans is TRUE?', '["They came from Europe on big ships","They never lived in Florida","They lived in America before European explorers came","They arrived in America after cars were invented"]', 2, 'Native Americans lived in America long before European explorers arrived.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Which of these groups lived in Florida long ago?', '["the Pilgrims","the Aztecs of Mexico","the Calusa","the Inca of Peru"]', 2, 'The Calusa were a Native people of South Florida.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.firstpeoples', NULL, 'Native American groups long ago made baskets and bowls out of ___.', '["plastic and steel","glass and rubber","clay and plant fibers","foam and wire"]', 2, 'Native peoples made baskets and pottery from clay and plant fibers.', 10),
  ('history', '3', 2, 'hist.3.florida', NULL, 'Florida is a state shaped like a long ___ that reaches into the ocean.', '["square","peninsula","circle","triangle"]', 1, 'Florida is a peninsula, with water on three sides.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Who is the leader of a state?', '["The principal","The president","The mayor","The governor"]', 3, 'A governor leads a state, like Florida.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Local governments provide services like ___.', '["movie stars","video games","candy","police, libraries, and parks"]', 3, 'Local governments run services such as police, libraries, and parks.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Why do communities make laws?', '["To keep people safe and treat them fairly","To use up paper","To confuse people","To make life boring"]', 0, 'Laws exist to keep people safe and make things fair.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What should you do if you think a rule is unfair?', '["Speak up and ask leaders to change it","Ignore everyone","Break it secretly","Do nothing ever"]', 0, 'In a fair community, people can speak up to change rules and laws.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'A ''right'' is something every person is free to ___.', '["buy only with gold","find in space","have or do","win in a contest"]', 2, 'Rights are freedoms that belong to every person.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Freedom of speech means you are allowed to ___.', '["only whisper","speak just one word a day","share your ideas","never talk"]', 2, 'Freedom of speech lets people share their ideas and opinions.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'The Statue of Liberty is a symbol of ___.', '["fast food","homework","winter","freedom"]', 3, 'The Statue of Liberty stands for freedom and welcome.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Who would you most likely ask to fix a broken park in your town?', '["A farmer in another state","Local government leaders","The president alone","A movie star"]', 1, 'Local government takes care of town services like parks.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Freedom of religion means people can ___.', '["only believe one thing","be forced to agree","never have beliefs","choose their own beliefs"]', 3, 'Freedom of religion lets people choose what to believe.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Good laws should treat people ___.', '["as a joke","fairly and equally","unkindly","differently for fun"]', 1, 'Fair laws treat all people equally.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'In the United States, who has the main job of making new laws for the whole country?', '["Congress","The Supreme Court","The army","The President"]', 0, 'Congress is the lawmaking branch of the federal government.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Why is it important for everyone to follow the same laws?', '["To make life harder for kids","So only rich people are happy","To keep people safe and treat them fairly","So no one can play games"]', 2, 'Laws help keep people safe and make sure everyone is treated fairly.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Which of these is an example of a law?', '["People must eat pizza","You should like the color blue","Everyone has to run fast","Drivers must stop at a red light"]', 3, 'Stopping at a red light is a real law that keeps people safe.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What is one reason a town might make a new law about wearing bike helmets?', '["To sell more candy","To help keep riders safe","To stop people from sleeping","To make bikes go faster"]', 1, 'Safety laws like helmet rules are made to protect people.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What do we call a law made by a city or town government?', '["A spelling test","A field trip","A local ordinance","A national holiday"]', 2, 'A local law made by a city or town is called an ordinance.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Who is the head leader of a city or town government?', '["The President","The mayor","A judge","A senator"]', 1, 'The mayor is the leader of a city or town.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Public schools in a town are usually run by the local ___.', '["candy store","football team","airport","school district"]', 3, 'Local school districts run the public schools in a town.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'A group of people elected to help the mayor run a city is often called the city ___.', '["kitchen","council","circus","forest"]', 1, 'A city council is a group elected to help make city decisions.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'The three levels of government in the United States are local, state, and ___.', '["ocean","summer","national","dessert"]', 2, 'The three levels are local, state, and national (federal).', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Local government taxes help pay for ___.', '["a trip to the moon","candy for the mayor","services like roads and schools","video games for one person"]', 2, 'Tax money pays for local services like roads and schools.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'A right is something every person is free to have or do, such as the freedom to ___.', '["skip all rules","share their ideas","fly without a plane","never go to bed"]', 1, 'Sharing ideas is part of the right to free speech.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Voting in elections is a right that lets citizens ___.', '["take money from a bank","skip all chores","drive any car","help choose their leaders"]', 3, 'Voting lets citizens help choose their leaders.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Rights in the United States are protected by the ___.', '["school bell","weather","Constitution","grocery store"]', 2, 'The Constitution protects the rights of people in the United States.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Which is a responsibility a citizen might do to help a neighbor?', '["Step on their flowers","Honk loudly at night","Hide their mail","Help carry their groceries"]', 3, 'Helping a neighbor shows responsibility and kindness.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'The bird that is the national symbol of the United States is the ___.', '["bald eagle","ostrich","penguin","chicken"]', 0, 'The bald eagle is the national bird and symbol of the United States.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'Which song is the national anthem of the United States?', '["Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star","Happy Birthday","The Star-Spangled Banner","The Wheels on the Bus"]', 2, 'The Star-Spangled Banner is the U.S. national anthem.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'Which building is a famous symbol where Congress meets to make laws?', '["A shopping mall","A water park","The United States Capitol","A baseball stadium"]', 2, 'The U.S. Capitol is where Congress meets to make laws.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'The state of Florida is nicknamed the ___ State.', '["Sunshine","Snow","Mountain","Desert"]', 0, 'Florida''s nickname is the Sunshine State.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'A new idea for a law that has not been passed yet is called a ___.', '["judge","vote","bill","county"]', 2, 'A bill is a proposed law before it is approved.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Which group makes the laws for the state of Florida?', '["The Supreme Court","The mayor of Miami","The Florida Legislature","The President of the United States"]', 2, 'The Florida Legislature makes state laws for Florida.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What can happen if a person breaks a law?', '["They get a free toy","They become the mayor","They may have to pay a fine or face a punishment","Nothing ever happens"]', 2, 'People who break laws can face fines or other punishments.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'A speed limit sign tells drivers the law about ___.', '["where they were born","what color to paint their car","how fast they may drive","how to cook dinner"]', 2, 'A speed limit is a law about how fast a driver may go.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Laws that keep our drinking water clean are made to protect ___.', '["cartoon characters","only the mayor","people''s health","the moon"]', 2, 'Clean water laws protect people''s health.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Florida is divided into local areas of government called ___.', '["counties","crayons","planets","oceans"]', 0, 'Florida is made up of counties, which are local areas of government.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Where does a city government usually meet to make decisions?', '["At the beach","In a treehouse","At city hall","On a school bus"]', 2, 'City governments often meet at city hall.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Public libraries in a community are usually paid for and run by ___.', '["a single child","a cartoon network","the local government","a sports star"]', 2, 'Local governments fund and run public libraries.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Keeping the roads in your town smooth and safe is a job for ___.', '["the President alone","a pet dog","a video game","local government"]', 3, 'Local government takes care of town roads.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'The capital city of Florida, where state government leaders work, is ___.', '["Miami","Tampa","Tallahassee","Orlando"]', 2, 'Tallahassee is the capital of Florida.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'A responsibility is a job or duty that a person should ___.', '["give to a pet","throw away","take care of","forget about"]', 2, 'A responsibility is a duty a person should take care of.', 10);
insert into public.questions (subject_id, grade, difficulty, skill, standard, prompt, choices, answer_index, explanation, xp) values
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Which action shows a responsible citizen taking care of the community?', '["Painting on a stop sign","Leaving trash everywhere","Yelling at neighbors","Picking up litter in the park"]', 3, 'Cleaning up litter shows responsibility for the community.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Which is an example of being a responsible student?', '["Breaking pencils","Hiding from class","Doing your homework","Teasing classmates"]', 2, 'Doing homework shows responsibility as a student.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Which is a responsibility that helps keep the Earth clean?', '["Recycling cans and bottles","Wasting water on purpose","Cutting down every tree","Pouring trash in rivers"]', 0, 'Recycling is a responsibility that helps keep the Earth clean.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Why should citizens stay informed about their community?', '["So they can make good choices and help out","So they never have to vote","So they can ignore problems","So they can break laws"]', 0, 'Staying informed helps citizens make good choices for their community.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'How many stripes are on the United States flag?', '["5","100","13","50"]', 2, 'The flag has 13 stripes for the first 13 colonies.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'What do Americans recite to show loyalty to the flag and country?', '["The Pledge of Allegiance","The alphabet","A grocery list","A jump rope rhyme"]', 0, 'The Pledge of Allegiance shows loyalty to the flag and country.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'A bald eagle holding an olive branch is shown on the Great Seal of the United States to stand for ___.', '["music","speed","peace","rain"]', 2, 'The olive branch on the seal is a symbol of peace.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'The Statue of Liberty was a gift to the United States from the country of ___.', '["Mexico","Egypt","Japan","France"]', 3, 'France gave the Statue of Liberty to the United States.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'Why do people show respect to the United States flag?', '["It is a toy","It tells time","It is a snack","It is a symbol of the country"]', 3, 'People respect the flag because it is a symbol of the country.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What usually happens to a bill before it can become a law?', '["It is sold in stores","Lawmakers vote on it","It is drawn as a picture","It is buried in the ground"]', 1, 'Lawmakers vote to decide if a bill becomes a law.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What is a person who helps make laws in Congress called?', '["A firefighter","A lawmaker","A farmer","A doctor"]', 1, 'People who help make laws are called lawmakers.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Laws and rules both tell people ___.', '["what dreams to have","how they should behave","how tall they will grow","what their favorite food is"]', 1, 'Laws and rules both guide how people should behave.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'The branch of government that makes laws is the ___ branch.', '["library","legislative","music","weather"]', 1, 'The legislative branch makes laws.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'If you wanted a new crosswalk near your school, who could you ask to help make that happen?', '["The President of France","A weather forecaster","Your local government leaders","A movie star"]', 2, 'Local leaders make decisions about things like crosswalks in your town.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Which service is usually provided by your local government?', '["Printing dollar bills","Choosing the President","Making the army","Trash pickup"]', 3, 'Local governments provide services like trash pickup.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Which level of government is closest to where you live every day?', '["Government of another country","Local government","The government of space","No government at all"]', 1, 'Local government is the level closest to your daily life.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Which of these is a local government service that helps in emergencies?', '["A roller coaster","The fire department","A toy store","A music band"]', 1, 'The fire department is a local service that helps in emergencies.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'How do citizens usually choose their mayor?', '["By voting in an election","By drawing pictures","By running a race","By flipping a coin"]', 0, 'Citizens choose their mayor by voting.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Which worker helps children cross the street safely near a school?', '["A chef","A pilot","A painter","A crossing guard"]', 3, 'A crossing guard helps children cross safely near schools.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Which of these is a responsibility of a good citizen?', '["Breaking windows","Following the laws","Littering in the park","Being unkind"]', 1, 'Following laws is a responsibility of a good citizen.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Why do citizens have both rights AND responsibilities?', '["So no one ever has to be kind","So people can be free and also take care of each other","So only adults matter","So rules can be ignored"]', 1, 'Rights give freedom while responsibilities help people care for one another.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Treating people of all backgrounds with fairness shows ___.', '["selfishness","meanness","laziness","respect"]', 3, 'Treating everyone fairly shows respect.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'What does it mean to respect other people''s rights?', '["Make fun of them","Let them have their freedoms too","Ignore the rules","Take away their turn"]', 1, 'Respecting rights means letting others enjoy their freedoms too.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'What is a fair way to settle a disagreement with a friend?', '["Refuse to ever speak again","Push the friend","Yell as loud as you can","Talk it out calmly"]', 3, 'Talking calmly is a fair, responsible way to solve disagreements.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'The 13 stripes on the United States flag stand for the first 13 ___.', '["colonies","kings","rivers","sports"]', 0, 'The 13 stripes represent the original 13 colonies.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'The Liberty Bell is an American symbol most connected to the idea of ___.', '["new shoes","fast food","liberty and freedom","summer vacation"]', 2, 'The Liberty Bell is a symbol of liberty and freedom.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'What should you do when the Pledge of Allegiance is said?', '["Run in circles","Stand and face the flag","Lie down and sleep","Sing a different song"]', 1, 'People stand and face the flag during the Pledge of Allegiance.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'What is the official flower of the state of Florida?', '["The tulip","The rose","The orange blossom","The sunflower"]', 2, 'The orange blossom is Florida''s state flower.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.symbols', NULL, 'Which monument honors the first President, George Washington, with a tall stone tower?', '["A windmill","The Washington Monument","A clock tower","A lighthouse"]', 1, 'The Washington Monument honors President George Washington.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'After Congress passes a bill, who can sign it to make it a law?', '["A mail carrier","A police officer","A teacher","The President"]', 3, 'The President signs bills from Congress to make them laws.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'If many lawmakers vote YES on a bill and only a few vote NO, the bill ___.', '["becomes a song","passes","turns into money","disappears"]', 1, 'A bill passes when more lawmakers vote yes than no.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Who decides the laws inside your own classroom?', '["The governor","The teacher, often with the class","A judge","The President"]', 1, 'Classroom rules are usually set by the teacher and students together.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'Why might lawmakers change an old law?', '["Because needs and times change","Because they ran out of paper","Because the sun is shining","Because it is someone''s birthday"]', 0, 'Laws can be changed when people''s needs change over time.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.lawmaking', NULL, 'What is the main purpose of laws in a community?', '["To stop the rain","To keep order and protect people","To make everyone the same age","To pick everyone''s clothes"]', 1, 'Laws keep order in a community and protect the people who live there.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Who keeps a town safe by stopping crime and helping people?', '["Astronauts","Police officers","Bakers","Movie actors"]', 1, 'Police officers help keep a town safe.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Who would most likely fix a broken streetlight on your road?', '["A famous singer","A pilot","The President","Local government workers"]', 3, 'Local government takes care of things like streetlights.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Who is the leader of a state''s government?', '["A teacher","The mayor","The governor","A crossing guard"]', 2, 'The governor is the leader of a state.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'Which place is run by the local government for people to play and relax?', '["A spaceship","A private bedroom","A volcano","A public park"]', 3, 'Local governments run public parks for the community.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.localgov', NULL, 'If your neighborhood needed a new bus stop, which level of government would you ask first?', '["No one","The army","Local government","The government of another country"]', 2, 'Local government handles things like neighborhood bus stops.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'Freedom of speech means people are allowed to ___.', '["skip school forever","never tell the truth","take other people''s things","say and share their ideas"]', 3, 'Freedom of speech lets people share their ideas and opinions.', 10),
  ('civics', '3', 2, 'civ.3.rights', NULL, 'What should a good citizen do when others are speaking?', '["Listen with respect","Shout over them","Cover their ears","Walk away rudely"]', 0, 'Listening with respect is part of being a good citizen.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'Scarcity means there is ___.', '["only candy","no such thing as choices","not enough for everyone''s wants","too much of everything"]', 2, 'Scarcity is when there isn''t enough to satisfy everyone''s wants.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'Because of scarcity, people must make ___.', '["noise","rain","mountains","choices"]', 3, 'Since we can''t have everything, scarcity forces us to choose.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A person who MAKES or sells goods is a ___.', '["tourist","producer","consumer","citizen"]', 1, 'A producer makes or provides goods and services.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A person who BUYS and uses goods is a ___.', '["producer","explorer","governor","consumer"]', 3, 'A consumer buys and uses goods and services.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'When you choose one thing, the thing you give up is called the ___.', '["prize","trade-off","bonus","refund"]', 1, 'A trade-off is what you give up when you make a choice.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'The money a person earns from working is called ___.', '["weather","income","a service","scarcity"]', 1, 'Income is the money you earn from a job.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'When a store sells out of a popular item, that is an example of ___.', '["plenty","saving","a service","scarcity"]', 3, 'Running out because there isn''t enough is scarcity.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A bakery that makes and sells cakes is acting as a ___.', '["producer","tourist","voter","consumer"]', 0, 'The bakery produces and sells goods, so it is a producer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Money you receive as a gift or allowance is also a kind of ___.', '["service","scarcity","income","tax"]', 2, 'Income is money you receive, including allowance or gifts.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'You have one dollar and want both a pencil and a sticker, but you can only buy one. What is this an example of?', '["Making a choice","Saving forever","Giving a gift","Earning money"]', 0, 'Because you cannot have both, you must pick one, which is making a choice.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Maya has $5. She wants a movie ticket for $5 and a snack for $3. Why can she not buy both?', '["Snacks are free","She does not have enough money","She has too much money","Tickets are free"]', 1, 'Together they cost $8, but she only has $5, so she must choose.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'A family has limited money. They should spend it FIRST on what?', '["Food and shelter","Movie tickets","New toys","Candy"]', 0, 'Needs like food and shelter come before wants when money is limited.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Which of these is a need for staying healthy?', '["A toy","Clean water","A new game","A poster"]', 1, 'Clean water is a need because your body must have it to stay healthy.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Why is it helpful to set a goal before saving money?', '["It stops you from earning","It makes money disappear","It helps you know what you are saving for","It makes things free"]', 2, 'A saving goal helps you stay focused on what you want to buy later.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What is income?', '["A kind of toy","A type of food","Money a person earns","Money a person throws away"]', 2, 'Income is the money a person earns, usually from working at a job.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Where can people safely keep their money to save it?', '["In a puddle","In the trash","In a bank","On the sidewalk"]', 2, 'A bank is a safe place to keep and save money.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'A taxi driver earns money by driving people places. That money is the driver''s what?', '["Income","Toy","Gift","Tax"]', 0, 'The money the driver earns from working is income.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'A nurse helps sick people and gets paid for it. The pay is called what?', '["Tax","Demand","Scarcity","Income"]', 3, 'The money the nurse earns from working is income.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Why might someone choose a job they are good at?', '["To never get paid","Jobs do not need any skill","To avoid working","They can do good work and earn income"]', 3, 'Doing a job well helps a person earn income.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A person who makes or sells goods is called a what?', '["Saver","Producer","Voter","Consumer"]', 1, 'A producer makes or sells goods and services.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'Which person is a consumer?', '["A worker building a house","A farmer planting corn","A baker making bread","A girl buying shoes at a store"]', 3, 'Buying shoes makes the girl a consumer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A toy company that designs and sells dolls is a what?', '["Consumer","Tourist","Producer","Student"]', 2, 'The company makes and sells dolls, so it is a producer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'Which of these is a service worker?', '["A bus driver","A pair of shoes","A bicycle","A loaf of bread"]', 0, 'A bus driver does work for people, providing a service.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'What does scarcity mean?', '["There is not enough of something for everyone","Everything is free","There is too much of everything","Nobody wants anything"]', 0, 'Scarcity means there is not enough of something to meet everyone''s wants.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'What is the word for how much people want to buy something?', '["Tax","Scarcity","Demand","Service"]', 2, 'Demand is how much people want to buy a good or service.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'If a fruit stand has lots of bananas and few people want them, what may happen to the price?', '["The price may go down","The stand earns more","Bananas become needs","The price must rise"]', 0, 'When supply is high and demand is low, prices often go down.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'If a new game is very popular and stores keep selling out, demand for the game is what?', '["Not real","Falling fast","Zero","High"]', 3, 'Selling out quickly shows that many people want it, so demand is high.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'If a toy store gets MORE of a popular toy that was sold out, the supply has done what?', '["Increased","Disappeared","Become a service","Stayed at zero"]', 0, 'Getting more of the toy means the supply increased.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'When supply is low and demand is high, an item is said to be what?', '["Useless","Free","Scarce","Plentiful"]', 2, 'Low supply with high demand means the item is scarce.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Why do people have to make choices about how to spend money?', '["Nobody likes anything","Everything is free","Money never runs out","Money is limited but wants are many"]', 3, 'People cannot buy everything, so they must choose what matters most.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Which is the BEST example of a want?', '["A doctor when sick","Drinking water","An amusement park trip","A warm coat in winter"]', 2, 'An amusement park trip is fun but not needed to live, so it is a want.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'A wise spender thinks about what before buying something?', '["Nothing at all","Whether they really need or want it","How fast to buy it","How to lose the money"]', 1, 'Good spenders think about whether an item is a need or a want first.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Lily wants a $10 toy but has $6. What is one smart choice?', '["Take a toy without paying","Save more money until she has enough","Give up on saving","Spend the $6 on something else by mistake"]', 1, 'Saving more money lets her reach her goal the right way.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'How do most adults earn income?', '["By sleeping all day","By losing money","By doing nothing","By working at a job"]', 3, 'People earn income by working at jobs and getting paid for it.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What is one job a person could do to earn income?', '["Teach students at a school","Watch clouds for free","Sleep all day","Lose their wallet"]', 0, 'Teaching is a job, and the teacher earns income for the work.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Banks help people by doing what with their saved money?', '["Throwing it out","Burning it","Spending it on candy","Keeping it safe"]', 3, 'A bank keeps people''s saved money safe until they need it.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What happens to money you put in a savings account over time at many banks?', '["It turns into candy","It becomes a toy","It disappears","It can grow a little with interest"]', 3, 'Banks often pay a little extra money called interest on savings.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What do taxes help pay for?', '["Nothing at all","Free candy for everyone","Public things like roads and schools","Only one person''s toys"]', 2, 'Taxes are money people pay so the government can fund roads, schools, and more.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A person who buys and uses goods is called a what?', '["Banker","Consumer","Producer","Mayor"]', 1, 'A consumer buys and uses goods and services.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A good is something you can do what to?', '["Only hear","Only smell","Touch and hold","Only feel as wind"]', 2, 'Goods are objects you can touch and hold.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'When a family pays for a plumber to fix a sink, the family is buying a what?', '["Service","Tax","Toy","Good"]', 0, 'The plumber does work for the family, which is a service.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A lemonade stand owner who makes and sells lemonade is a what?', '["Producer","Consumer","Banker","Mayor"]', 0, 'Making and selling lemonade makes the owner a producer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'Because of scarcity, people must do what?', '["Make choices","Throw money away","Get everything they want","Stop working"]', 0, 'Since resources are limited, scarcity forces people to make choices.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'What is the word for how much of a good is available to sell?', '["Demand","Tax","Income","Supply"]', 3, 'Supply is how much of a good is available to sell.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'What do we call the things people use to make goods, like wood and water?', '["Taxes","Services","Banks","Resources"]', 3, 'Resources are the materials people use to make goods.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'Which sentence about scarcity is true?', '["It never happens","It means there is too much","It affects every person and country","It only affects children"]', 2, 'Scarcity affects everyone because resources are always limited.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Which sentence best describes a need?', '["Something you can skip","Something you must have to live","Something only rich people use","Something extra and fun"]', 1, 'Needs are things people must have to live, like food, water, and shelter.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What is a good reason to save part of your income?', '["To make it vanish","To buy something bigger later","To pay more taxes for fun","To never use it"]', 1, 'Saving income lets you afford bigger things in the future.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'If you spend ALL your income right away, what can you no longer do?', '["Eat any food","Go to school","See your family","Save for the future"]', 3, 'Spending all income means there is nothing left to save.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A farmer who grows and sells apples is acting as a what?', '["Tourist","Consumer","Student","Producer"]', 3, 'The farmer makes and sells goods, so the farmer is a producer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A doctor who checks your health is providing a what?', '["Good","Toy","Service","Tax"]', 2, 'A doctor provides a service by doing helpful work for people.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'Which of these workers provides a service?', '["A bakery making pies","A mail carrier delivering letters","A factory making cans","A farm growing wheat"]', 1, 'Delivering mail is helpful work, which is a service.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'Which sentence is true about consumers?', '["They never use anything","They buy goods and services","They grow all their own food","They only make goods"]', 1, 'Consumers are people who buy goods and services to use.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'A store sells out of a popular toy and cannot get more. This is an example of what?', '["Saving","Taxes","Scarcity","Income"]', 2, 'Running out with no more available shows scarcity.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'Why can''t people have everything they want?', '["People are lazy","Stores are closed","Money is endless","Resources are limited"]', 3, 'Resources like money, time, and goods are limited, so wants cannot all be met.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'Scarcity happens when wants are greater than what?', '["The size of a town","The resources available","The number of people","The day of the week"]', 1, 'Scarcity means wants are bigger than the limited resources available.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'A snowstorm stops trucks from bringing milk to a town. The milk supply has done what?', '["Become free","Gone down","Gone up","Become a want"]', 1, 'If milk cannot be delivered, less is available, so supply goes down.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'When you choose to buy a book instead of a toy, the toy you gave up is called the what?', '["Tax","Opportunity cost","Income","Service"]', 1, 'The opportunity cost is the next best thing you give up when you make a choice.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Which choice shows good money planning?', '["Never thinking about cost","Saving some money before spending it all","Throwing money away","Spending every penny right away"]', 1, 'Saving some money first is a smart way to plan for the future.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'Ben can play soccer OR ride his bike, but not both today. What does he have to do?', '["Earn income","Pay a tax","Make a choice","Buy a service"]', 2, 'Since he cannot do both, he must choose one activity.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.choices', NULL, 'When you decide to do one thing, you give up the chance to do another. The thing given up is the what?', '["Reward","Allowance","Bonus","Opportunity cost"]', 3, 'Opportunity cost is the best thing you give up when you choose.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Money you get as an allowance for chores is a kind of what?', '["Loan","Tax","Service","Income"]', 3, 'Allowance money you earn for chores is a kind of income.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What does it mean to save money?', '["To keep money to use later","To give it all away","To hide it and forget it","To spend it all today"]', 0, 'Saving means keeping money now so you can use it later.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Why do people go to work?', '["To avoid all jobs","To stop earning","To make money disappear","To earn income for their needs and wants"]', 3, 'People work to earn income so they can buy needs and wants.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'What is a budget?', '["A plan for how to use your money","A type of job","A kind of bank","A free toy"]', 0, 'A budget is a plan that shows how you will spend and save money.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.income', NULL, 'Why is it important to keep money in a safe place?', '["So it can get wet","So you forget about it","So it gets dirty","So it is not lost or stolen"]', 3, 'Keeping money safe, like in a bank, protects it from being lost or stolen.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'When you buy a sandwich at a shop, you are acting as a what?', '["Producer","Builder","Farmer","Consumer"]', 3, 'Buying and eating the sandwich makes you a consumer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A factory that builds bikes is acting as a what?', '["Consumer","Producer","Saver","Shopper"]', 1, 'The factory makes goods, so it is a producer.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'Producers and consumers depend on each other because producers make things and consumers do what?', '["Ignore them","Buy them","Hide them","Throw them away"]', 1, 'Consumers buy what producers make, so they need each other.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A person can be both a producer and a consumer because they can do what?', '["Only travel","Never work","Only sleep","Make things and also buy things"]', 3, 'People often make goods at work and buy goods as shoppers too.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.producerconsumer', NULL, 'A music teacher who gives piano lessons is providing a what?', '["Snack","Service","Good","Toy"]', 1, 'Teaching lessons is helpful work, which is a service.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'If many people want a toy but there are only a few left, what often happens to the price?', '["The toy becomes free","The store closes forever","The price drops to zero","The price may go up"]', 3, 'When many people want something that is scarce, the price often goes up.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'During a drought, there is not enough water. This is an example of what?', '["Income","Plenty","A service","Scarcity"]', 3, 'Not having enough water for everyone is scarcity.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'A bakery has only 10 cupcakes but 30 children want one. This shows what?', '["Plenty for all","Free goods","No demand","Scarcity"]', 3, 'There are not enough cupcakes for everyone, so this is scarcity.', 10),
  ('economics', '3', 2, 'econ.3.scarcity', NULL, 'When something is scarce, what must people decide?', '["To waste it all","To ignore it","How to make it free","Who gets it and how to use it"]', 3, 'Scarcity makes people decide how to share and use limited things.', 10),
